description:
Horror film icon Bela Lugosi is your host for this anthology of creepy stories in the classic horror comics tradition. Join Bela and his sexy companion Nosferina for 52 pages of horrific fun that includes seven complete stories by top comics artists and writers, a Lugosi portrait gallery, an article by Lugosi authority Gary Rhodes, cover art by legendary monster painter Basil Gogos and a variant cover by fan favorite John Cassaday. Produced with the cooperation of the Bela Lugosi estate.

description:
The Legend Dies

The legend was born in the flames of battle on the Normandy Beach... Lr. Moose Amberg, never in combat before, emerged from the first week of fighting as the hero of his company! No obstacle the Nazis put up could stop the ex-pro football player! Moose Amberg laughed at death... and attacked... and attacked... and won time and time again! Moose Amberg's legend was growing then!

Carry the Mail!

Sgt. Klein's job looked like a racket to the G.I.'s in his outfit -- he had the mail run, picking up mail and orders at Tunis, delivering them across 400 miles of desert to division H.Q. and occasionally, he had to take a replacement in with him..

The Stupid P.F.C.

They all called the kid stoop... short for stupid... and Dan J. Monahan was probably the dumbest G.I. ever shipped to the S.T.O.! For instance, it was stoop Monahan, PFC, who used his flashlight to look for a dropped grenade... with the German artillery zeroed in on the Belgian road they were checking! The Nazi gunners wasted no time...
name: The Legend Dies; Carry the Mail!; The Stupid P.F.C.
